		"episodes": [
			{
				"id": "ep-001",
				"slug": "the-system-is-working-as-designed",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "The System Is Working — As Designed",
					"episode_number": 1,
					"season_number": 1,
					"cover_art": {
						"$media": {
							"url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573164574572-cb89e39749b4?w=1200&h=675&fit=crop",
							"alt": "Fire against dark sky",
							"filename": "ep001-cover.jpg"
						}
					},
					"youtube_video_id": "",
					"audio_url": "",
					"audio_file_size": 0,
					"audio_duration": "1:02:14",
					"excerpt": "In our debut episode, we lay out the thesis: the systems causing suffering aren't broken — they're doing exactly what they were built to do. And that changes everything about how we fight them.",
					"show_notes": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [{ "_type": "span", "text": "Episode Notes" }]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "In this debut episode, we dig into the foundational question: are unjust systems broken, or are they working exactly as intended? The answer shapes every strategy for change."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [{ "_type": "span", "text": "Resources Mentioned" }]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "Michelle Alexander — The New Jim Crow"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "Keeanga-Yamahtta Taylor — From #BlackLivesMatter to Black Liberation"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "Angela Davis — Are Prisons Obsolete?"
								}
							]
						}
					],
					"transcript": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "[Full transcript will be available within 48 hours of release.]"
								}
							]
						}
					]
				},
				"bylines": [{ "byline": "byline-hosts" }],
				"taxonomies": {
					"topic": ["politics", "racial-justice"]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "ep-002",
				"slug": "housing-is-a-human-right",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "Housing Is a Human Right — So Why Don't We Treat It Like One?",
					"episode_number": 2,
					"season_number": 1,
					"cover_art": {
						"$media": {
							"url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558618666-fcd25c85cd64?w=1200&h=675&fit=crop",
							"alt": "Protest signs at a housing demonstration",
							"filename": "ep002-cover.jpg"
						}
					},
					"youtube_video_id": "",
					"audio_url": "",
					"audio_file_size": 0,
					"audio_duration": "58:31",
					"excerpt": "The housing crisis isn't a market failure — it's a policy choice. We trace how housing became a commodity and what movements around the world are doing to fight back.",
					"show_notes": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [{ "_type": "span", "text": "Episode Notes" }]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "This week we trace the history of housing as a right and how deliberate policy choices created today's crisis. From rent control to public housing to tenant organizing, what actually works?"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [{ "_type": "span", "text": "Resources Mentioned" }]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "Peter Marcuse — The Language of Gentrification"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"text": "Samuel Stein — Capital City: Gentrification and the Real Estate State"
								}
							]
						}
					],
					"transcript": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
